    Scope and Contents
Energy Studies Records (1976-85) consist of announcements, brochures New &amp; Expanded program requests, memos regarding the Energy Task Force, and proposals for an energy administration program.  This series also contains reports on the "Community Energy Self-Reliance Springfield Energy Project" (1982)  including citizen participation, electricity demand, transportation study, and summary &amp;  task force reports.  The Energy Studies is an area of study within the School of Public Affairs and Administration.  The goal of energy studies is to develop a synthesis of technical knowledge and social considerations to study energy issues and to seek solutions to energy problems.  
  
